post_text:
Dear Parents,

Welcome to the Carbondale Area School District official Facebook page. We will use this format as another method of keeping you informed of any special activities or happenings that we have going on at our district. Please check back often for updated messages regarding extracurricular events, weather related information, and any other pertinent information.

We thank you for your support of our district.

post_text:
REMINDER

STUDENT IPAD & CHARGER HAND-IN WILL BE TOMORROW TUESDAY JUNE 16th FROM 10AM – NOON IN THE BACK OF THE HIGH SCHOOL BUILIDNG.

ANYONE CAN RETURN THE IPADS BACK TO THE SCHOOL, IT DOES NOT NEED TO BE A PARENT AND/OR GUARDIAN LIKE WE NEEDED DURING DISTRIBUTION.

PLEASE PULL AROUND BACK AND STAY IN YOUR VERHICLE. WE WILL BE COMING TO YOUR VEHICAL TO RETREIVE THE IPAD & CHARGER.

PLEASE MAKE SURE YOU HAVE THE IPAD CHARGER WITH YOU WHEN YOU RETURN YOUR IPAD.

LAST, PLEASE CLEAN & DISINFECT THE IPAD & CHARGER PRIOR TO RETURNING IT AND MAKE SURE IT HAS A CHARGE SO THAT WE CAN CHECK THE IPAD FOR ANY DAMAGE.

THANK YOU AND WE WILL SEE YOU ALL BETWEEN 10AM AND NOON TOMORROW TUESDAY JUNE 16TH.

post_text:
Attention all current Sophomores:

Lackawanna Leadership

Current Sophomores can apply for the Tomorrow's Leaders Today [TLT] Program

Our Tomorrow’s Leaders Today program develops the leadership, interpersonal and managerial skills of high school juniors and provides real-world experiences in the areas of philanthropy, non-profit organizations and community service. Sessions are held one full weekday each month. Leadership Lackawanna’s Tomorrow’s Leaders Today Program accepts applications from sophomores who attend high school in Lackawanna County or in the Lackawanna Trail and Western Wayne school districts.

Application deadline is May 15th.
Applications are available on www.LeadershipLackawanna.com.

Leadership Lackawanna is extremely sensitive to the current situation of our country, however, we would like to proceed forward with accepting applications for our youth initiatives – Tomorrow’s Leaders Today and Leadership U. These programs are not scheduled to begin until July and mid-October, however, we do have the technology in place should we need to teach remotely.

Attention all CA Seniors:

SENIOR DECISION DAY ( May 1st ) – Any senior planning on going to college, trade school or the military in the fall should submit a picture of yourself wearing a shirt or sweatshirt of yourself from the school or branch of service that you will be attending in the Fall. Because the pictures will be placed in the yearbook and hopefully on a video that we will place on our web page, we are asking that you take the picture in your school uniform bottoms, just as if you were taking the picture here in school. Once the picture is taken, please submit it to our yearbook adviser, Mr. Foote at corey.foote@carbondalearea.org

Submission deadline is Monday April 27th.

post_text: The Carbondale Area School District was able to help feed over 400 families today during our meal distribution. The district would like to thank all our essential staff who have been making our meal distribution possible. Today our essential employees dealt with the torrential downpours along with some equipment issues but were still able to get the job done for our families. The district is making sure that all equipment is operational, and meals will be ready for our next meal distribution next week, Tuesday April 14th. Thank you all for your cooperation and support.

post_text:
Dear Parents and Community Members,

I would like to remind you that there will be no school this Monday (May 27th, 2019) in remembrance of Memorial Day.

I know this holiday is associated with the beginning of the summer season and I am sure many of us will take advantage of the extended weekend to enjoy the beautiful weather, perhaps travel a bit, or have a cookout to welcome the long awaited warmer temperatures.

I would like to take a moment and honor those brave men and women who made the ultimate sacrifice for us to enjoy the freedom’s that this wonderful country has to offer. As I walk through our buildings and drive through our city, I am reminded that our community has lost some of our own residences while serving on active duty.

To our local families who have lost loved ones, I wish you comfort and peace and thank you for reminding us what the true meaning of Memorial Day is about.

Have a wonderful weekend and I look forward to welcoming our students back on Tuesday.

Bob

post_text:
Dear parents,

A short while ago both our elementary and secondary buildings participated in a restrictive movement and lock down drill.

This drill was a part of our requirements under the safe schools act as well as our desire to make sure our staff and students are well prepared in the event of an actual emergency.

I want to assure you that there was no threat in any of our buildings or on our campus and it was merely an exercise in school safety management.

We will continue to hold such drills and the school will follow up with you upon completion of the drill.

Thank you for your support of the Carbondale area school district and I wish you a wonderful weekend

Mr. Mehalick

post_text:
Dear Parents,

In an effort to keep our elementary students who are on "parent pick-up" safe at dismissal, we are asking anyone who is picking up their child at the end of the day to please park in an open parking space. There are spaces available, especially in the lower part of the parking lot. We cannot have cars double-parked and blocking in cars that are legally parked. This practice creates a dangerous situation for students and family members who are walking back to their vehicle.

Our police officers will be visible in the parking lot at dismissal and will be available to assist you if you should have any questions regarding where you can park.

I appreciate your cooperation and understanding in the reason for implementing this change.

Thank you,

Bob

post_text:
Good Evening,

I want to inform you that Carbondale Area will be operating on a 3 hour delay for Friday February 1st 2019.

Parents its been some time since we called a 3 hour delay so please note that elementary will start at 10:50am and our high school will begin at 11:00am.
All bus stop times will be 3 hours later than normal.

Please note with the three hour delay we will not serve breakfast.

Warming temperatures are expected for next week so lets all hope we do not have many more weather related disruptions and please join me in hoping that Punxstuawney Phil does not see his shadow this year.

I wish you all a wonderful evening, and a great Superbowl weekend.

Thank you for your support of our wonderful district.

Bob

Dear Parents/Guardians,

Due to the threat of inclement weather late Thursday evening into Friday morning; and the potential for that causing a delay, we will be canceling our in-service and Friday will now be a regular school day.

In the event that the weather does not cause a delay, we will still operate Friday as a regular school day with dismissal at our normal times.

Please note we will now hold our in-service day on Friday February 8th and will be operating on an early dismissal.
We will send out a reminder closer to that date.

Thank you,
Bob

post_text:
Dear Parents and members of our community;

I want to inform you that this morning Mr. Farrell and Officer Golay were notified that a high school student was thought to be in possession of a weapon.
The student and their belongings were immediately searched, and a toy weapon was confiscated.
I want you to know that there was no real weapon or danger to any of our students or staff members.
I also want you to know that we are treating this as a very serious threat against our school community and we are in contacted with both the Carbondale Police department and the District Attorney’s office and will cooperate fully with them on this matter.

Thank you for your support.

Bob Mehalick

post_text:
Dear Parents and Students,

I would like to announce two exciting incentive programs that we will be initiating for our students.

1. All students in grades (K-12) who have perfect attendance during the 45 day marking period will be treated to a special breakfast meal prepared by our food service vendor. We will offer this incentive beginning with this marking period which ends on November 1st.

For any student who receives perfect attendance for all four marking periods, they will be treated to a breakfast at one of our local restaurants.

It is imperative that our students are attending school regularly and that we instill in them the importance of being responsible to their academics.

2. Our second incentive program will be for our secondary students in grades 9-12th. Any student who has 93% or higher in any subject area which requires a final examination, will have the option of being exempt from their final examination. The exemption will be at the discretion of the student, so if a student attains a 93% or higher and wish to take the final, they can.
text:
Dear Parents and Students,

I would like to announce two exciting incentive programs that we will be initiating for our students.

1. All students in grades (K-12) who have perfect attendance during the 45 day marking period will be treated to a special breakfast meal prepared by our food service vendor. We will offer this incentive beginning with this marking period which ends on November 1st.

For any student who receives perfect attendance for all four marking periods, they will be treated to a breakfast at one of our local restaurants.

It is imperative that our students are attending school regularly and that we instill in them the importance of being responsible to their academics.

2. Our second incentive program will be for our secondary students in grades 9-12th. Any student who has 93% or higher in any subject area which requires a final examination, will have the option of being exempt from their final examination. The exemption will be at the discretion of the student, so if a student attains a 93% or higher and wish to take the final, they can.

post_text:
Dear Parents,

The Carbondale Area Administration would like to inform you that we have been investigating reports of threats to our school. These threats have been investigated thoroughly by the Carbondale Police as well as our Director of School Safety and Security, Officer Michael Golay.

At this time, our investigation has determined the threats are not credible and that our students were not in any danger at any time.

We met with the entire secondary student body this morning and stressed to them that if they hear or see anything that causes them concern to immediately report the activity to a member of our staff.

We will continue to monitor and investigate any threats to the well-being of our school community, and want to ensure you that the safety and security of your child is our top priority.

Please do not hesitate to contact me if you should have any concerns.

Thank you,

Mr. Robert F. Mehalick

post_text:
Dear Parents,

This afternoon we were informed that a group of our students were planning a walk-out tomorrow to get their message of school safety out to the public.
I want to first assure you that myself and our entire administration team, support our student’s rights to be heard. We are however, asking our students, to hold off their demonstration until the national walk-out day, so we can have police onsite to also ensure that those who are demonstrating are safe.
As Superintendent, I am proud that our students feel the desire to be heard and speak out about this very important topic. I also want to ensure you that school safety is out top priority.
I ask you to please encourage your child to stay inside the building and their opportunity to demonstrate will be granted on National Walk-out day if they choose to be a part.

Thank you for your support of our district.

Bob

post_text:
Hello Carbondale Area Community,

I want to remind those wishing to volunteer in our schools, that the spring window for submitting your clearances is open. We will be accepting clearances from parents and family members who wish to volunteer in our schools until January 31st. If you are planning on volunteering for upcoming Field Trips, Activities, and Clubs, you must have your State Police, FBI, and Child Abuse Clearance’s and provide them to Mrs. Mary Carachilo in our Elementary Office.

If the district does not have a copy of your clearances by January 31st you will not be able to volunteer until the next window period which will be August 20th.
The district requires a copy for our records, and we recommend you maintain the originals so you also have record. We will not be able to make copies from our office.

We thank you for wanting to volunteer in our schools and appreciate your understanding of this process, as it is to maintain the safety of our students.

Have a wonderful day!

Bob

We thank you for wanting to volunteer in our schools and appreciate your understanding of this process, as it is to maintain the safety of our students.

Have a wonderful day!

Bob

Carbondale Area School District
January 8, 2018 at 12:15 PM ·

Dear Parents,

I would like to inform you that at approximately 7:10am this morning (Monday January 8th), one of our boilers, which heats the 3rd through 6th grade hallway, briefly malfunctioned and we lost heat to that area of the building. Our maintenance staff were able to get the boiler working again within 45 minutes and the rooms and hallways had appropriate heat by 8:00am and the temperature back to normal by approximately 8:30am.

We will continue to monitor this situation and hopefully this will not be an issue going forward.

We apologize for any short-term discomfort to our students and staff.

Have a great day,

Bob
